    <section class="research-section" id="aboutresearch">
        <h3 class="section-header">The Research</h3>
        <p>Due to the nature of healthcare provision, more ergonomic technology can help improve the lives of both healthcare providers and patients. In 2019, U.S. hospitals reported 221,400 work-related injuries or illnesses - furthermore, given the lengthy and demanding work hours of healthcare providers, maintaining energy levels for patient care is critical. Equipment uncomfortable to use and/or maintain, or injuries from said use diminish this energy. In addition, in 2022, 46% of health workers reported feeling burnt out or exhausted - part of this may have resulted from the daily handling of this uncomfortable-to-use equipment. Thus, using more comfortable, easy-to-use equipment may ease and/or partially solve the previously stated problems.</p>
        <p> The better healthcare professionals can do their work, the overall more healthy society will be. Thus, a smaller, more comfortable and easy-to-use technology, which replaces several bulky, hard-to-use machines will have a massive impact on society in the long-run. </p>
        <p>For the patients, comfort is of utmost importance as it positively influences their well-being and their perception of the overall process, possibly leading to faster recovery and improved health. Thus, uncomfortable equipment can compromise a patient’s health in the long run. Therefore, the better and more comfortable hospital equipment (such as the Apollon) is, the better the overall health of patients, and by extension the better the health of the community. Improved health can have an abundance of positive long-term consequences, including but not limited to increased mental health, happiness, and productivity; All of these impacts massively influence society.
        <p>In conclusion, there is a need to develop comfortable, easy-to-use hospital equipment because  of the huge impact this technology will have on society. New equipment such as the Apollon will provide comfort to both healthcare providers and patients, enhancing the physical and mental health of both.</p> </p>
